The paper deals with rate and power allocation in a fading multiple-access channel, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses optimization of a utility function, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of channel statistics and power control also suggests a possible connection to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents results for general concave utility functions, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
